1 § 4093. KRATOM PRODUCT REGISTRATION
2 (a) A processor or distributor shall register annually with the Department
3 any kratom product that is in an approved kratom delivery form intended to be
4 offered for sale or distributed to a consumer in the State. The registering
5 processor or distributor shall pay a fee to the Department, subject to annual
6 adjustment, to cover all administrative costs for processing and administering
7 registrations and developing and maintaining a kratom product registry
8 webpage on the Department’s website. The processor or distributor’s
9 registration application shall include:
10 (1) sworn assurances from the processor or distributor that that any
11 facility in which the kratom product was prepared, manufactured, or
12 maintained has a valid food facility registration with the U.S. Food and Drug
13 Administration;
14 (2) evidence demonstrating that the processor or distributor has a
15 reasonable basis for believing the kratom product is safe for consumption
16 under the conditions of use set forth on the product’s label;
17 (3) a certificate of analysis from an independent testing laboratory
18 showing compliance with the requirements for kratom products in accordance
19 with this subchapter; and
